Hello, and welcome back to Miracle Fly! Here are the voting results this time: 1 vote for YouTube to not take away our ability to annotate, 1 vote for Super Mario V, 1 vote for Tuxedo Mask Irvette, 1 vote for 7-C, and 4 votes for 7-9!

So, she'll start off by tossing red crescent shots, which fly horizontally until they line up with you, at which point they'll move vertically towards you.
Most of the Lumina fight isn't too tricky, aside from the 3rd and 4th anger phases, so if you're good at those, this might be a good place to farm stars.
If I tried hard enough, I could've gotten to the 2nd anger phase before she even dropped to the floor there.
Here's the first anger phase at 20% damage, as usual. Lumina will fire six of those red crescents in a row. Start in the lower-left corner, and move slowly right as the shots come to dodge them all.
Interestingly, boxes that are on fire won't actually just burn to nothingness over time. They'll only be destroyed when hit with your shots or a couple fireballs from other sources.
This way, his fireballs will break a hole through the cracked blocks obstructing this gem, which you cannot break through yourself.

If a flame bat touches a group of regular breakable boxes, that entire group will catch fire. While on fire, it hurts to touch them (obviously), and destroying them causes fireballs to shoot out in orthogonal directions.
Lumina will also travel around the room from corner to corner, although she won't go all the way up to the ceiling corners, and be more like 2/3 up the wall instead.

Okay, 4th anger phase at 80% damage: She'll go to the upper-right corner and fire 14 crescents in a row, alternating between red and green. This could be a thing.

3rd anger phase at 60% damage: Lumina will go to the upper-right corner and fire off 15 crescents in a row, with most of them being green. This is really tricky, and I usually take a hit here.
Also, she starts firing green crescents which start off moving vertically, then turn horizontally when they line up with you. But, just like the red ones, they can only change direction once.
2nd anger phase at 40% damage: She'll drop to the lower-right corner, and fire off nine red crescents in a row. Start in the lower-left corner, fly to the ceiling, and then go right to dodge them.
